data.title: BBC One's EastEnders star Jessie Wallace reportedly engaged
data.meta_description: BBC One’s Eastenders star Jessie Wallace, who plays Kat Slater is said to be engaged.
data.text:
The actress plays the icon Kat Slater on the soap and has seen Wallace engaged and married multiple times as the once-landlady.

However, it will be the first time that Wallace will be a bride off-screen, after reports that her boyfriend Justin Gallwey popped the big question.

The exciting news comes after the EastEnders actress was seen wearing an engagement ring whilst out shopping in North London.

EastEnders star Jessie Wallace engaged

As The Sun claims the couple are expected to marry after at least a year together.

The couple had previously created confusion among fans after hinting they had already tied the knot.

After Wallace posted a photo of the pair, writing the caption ‘My Hubby’, seeing co-stars comment ‘So happy for you both’ and ‘You look so happy’.

Fans were quick to share their excitement but the couple denied the rumours as Gallwey said it was “just a term of endearment”.
